trans-unit.source: Provides a user interface for selecting a file name.
<xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.FileNameEditor> provides a file selection dialog box for file name selection and editing.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.Design.FileNameEditor"></xref> class.
Edits the specified object using the editor style provided by the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.Design.FileNameEditor.GetEditStyle(System.ComponentModel.ITypeDescriptorContext)"></xref> method.
A service provider is provided so that any required editing services can be obtained.
An <xref href="System.ComponentModel.ITypeDescriptorContext"></xref> that can be used to gain additional context information.
A service provider object through which editing services may be obtained.
An instance of the value being edited.
The new value of the object.
If the value of the object hasn't changed, this should return the same object it was passed.

Gets the editing style used by the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.Design.FileNameEditor.EditValue(System.ComponentModel.ITypeDescriptorContext,System.IServiceProvider,System.Object)"></xref> method.
If the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Design.FileNameEditor.EditValue%2A> method is not supported, this method will return <xref:System.Drawing.Design.UITypeEditorEditStyle.None>.
An <xref href="System.ComponentModel.ITypeDescriptorContext"></xref> that can be used to gain additional context information.
One of the <xref href="System.Drawing.Design.UITypeEditorEditStyle"></xref> values indicating the provided editing style.
Initializes the open file dialog when it is created.
This method configures the dialog box with a generic file filter and title.
The <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.OpenFileDialog"></xref> to use to select a file name.
